sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as Next.js Frontend
    participant Backend as FastAPI Backend
    participant Agents as Multi-Agent System
    participant Tools as Tool System
    participant SDK as Databricks SDK
    participant Workspace as Databricks Workspace
    participant Lakebase as Lakebase DB
    participant Cache as Redis Cache
    
    User->>Frontend: "Analyze job 123"
    
    Note over Frontend: Step 1: User Request
    
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/chat/messages<br/>{message, conversation_id}
    
    Note over Backend: Step 2: API Processing
    
    Backend->>Backend: Authenticate user
    Backend->>Lakebase: Load conversation history
    Lakebase-->>Backend: Previous messages
    
    Backend->>Agents: Route to appropriate agent
    
    Note over Agents: Step 3: Agent Processing
    
    Agents->>Tools: execute_tool("resolve_job", {job_id: 123})
    
    Tools->>SDK: GET /api/2.0/jobs/get?job_id=123
    SDK->>Workspace: API Request
    Workspace-->>SDK: Job metadata
    SDK-->>Tools: Job data
    
    Tools->>Cache: Check cache (key: job:123)
    
    alt Cache hit
        Cache-->>Tools: Cached result
    else Cache miss
        Tools->>SDK: GET /api/2.0/jobs/runs/list
        SDK->>Workspace: API Request
        Workspace-->>SDK: Job runs data
        SDK-->>Tools: Runs data
        
        Tools->>Cache: Store in cache (TTL: 5min)
        Tools-->>Agents: Tool result
    end
    
    Note over Agents: Step 4: Generate Response
    
    Agents->>Agents: Process results, generate recommendations
    Agents->>Lakebase: Persist conversation
    Lakebase-->>Agents: ✓ Saved
    
    Agents-->>Backend: FinalOutputEvent
    
    Note over Backend: Step 5: Stream Response
    
    Backend->>Frontend: SSE: final_output<br/>{recommendations, metadata}
    Frontend->>User: Display results
    
    Note over User: Data flow complete<br/>Request → Processing → Storage → Response

